# MegaMek-Web Licensing Information

This project uses a dual-licensing approach to properly attribute and comply with
upstream MegaMek project licensing requirements.

## License Overview

1. **Apache License 2.0** for all original source code
2. **Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0)** for game data and assets derived from MegaMek

## Code License Details

All original source code in this repository is licensed under the Apache License 2.0.

**What this means:**

- You can use, modify, and distribute the code
- You must provide attribution to the original authors
- You must include the license notice in distributions
- Full license text: [LICENSE.code](LICENSE.code)

**Applies to:**

- All `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.js` files in `src/`
- Build scripts and configuration files
- Original documentation in `docs/` and `openspec/`
- Any other original program code

## Data/Assets License Details

All game data and assets derived from the MegaMek project are licensed under CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0.

**What this means:**

- You can share and adapt the materials
- You must give appropriate credit to the MegaMek project
- You **cannot** use the materials for commercial purposes
- You must license derivatives under CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0 or compatible
- Full license text: [LICENSE.assets](LICENSE.assets)

**Applies to:**

- Unit data files in `public/data/units/` (converted from MegaMek MTF format)
- Record sheet templates and SVG assets in `public/record-sheets/`
- Equipment data in `public/data/equipment/` derived from MegaMek
- Any other game data or artwork derived from the MegaMek project

## Directory Structure

The licenses apply to the following:

| Directory | License |
|-----------|---------|
| `src/` | Apache 2.0 |
| `scripts/` | Apache 2.0 |
| `openspec/` | Apache 2.0 |
| `docs/` | Apache 2.0 |
| `desktop/` | Apache 2.0 |
| `public/data/units/` | CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0 |
| `public/data/equipment/` | CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0 (derived data) |
| `public/record-sheets/` | CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0 |

## Attribution

### MegaMek Project

Unit data files are converted from MegaMek/MegaMekLab project data files.
Record sheet templates and pip graphics are derived from MegaMek project assets.

- **Project:** MegaMek (https://megamek.org)
- **Repository:** https://github.com/MegaMek
- **Original License:** CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0 for data/assets, GPLv3 for code

### BattleTech Intellectual Property

